<TITLE> Tahrir activist detained in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)Chittagong police on Friday arrested an activist of banned Islamist outfit Hizb ut-Tahrir while he was distributing leaflets. Mozzammel Hossain Manik, 20, son of Ashraf Ali of Padua village of Lohagara upazila, works at a shop at Reazuddin Bazar of the city. Chittagong Sadr Police sub-inspector Nasir Uddin said they had arrested Maink in front of Golam Rashul Jame Mosque when he was distributing leaflets among the devotees after Juma prayers. The police officer also said legal steps would be taken against the Tahrir activist. The Islamist outfit, in its leaflet, urged the countrymen to oust the ruling party. bdnew
